http://purl.org/dc/terms/title.value: Earth Resource Material Role - All Concepts

http://purl.org/dc/terms/source.value: Glossary of Geology. 5th Edition, AGI - online

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: (a) Any change in the mineralogic composition of a rock brought about by physical or chemical means, esp. by the action of hydrothermal solutions; also, a secondary, i.e. supergene, change in a rock or mineral. (b) Changes in the chemical or mineralogical composition of a rock produced by weathering.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/source.value: Glossary of Geology. 5th Edition, AGI - online

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: The valueless rock or mineral aggregates in an ore; that part of an ore that is not economically desirable but cannot be avoided in mining. It is separated from the ore minerals during concentration

http://purl.org/dc/terms/source.value: Glossary of Geology. 5th Edition, AGI - online

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: A body of rock serving as a host for other rocks or for mineral deposits; e.g. a pluton containing xenoliths, or any rock in which ore deposits occur. It is a somewhat more specific term than country rock.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/source.value: Glossary of Geology. 5th Edition, AGI - online

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: The naturally occurring material from which a mineral or minerals of economic value can be extracted at a reasonable profit. Also, the mineral(s) thus extracted. The term is generally but not always used to refer to metalliferous material, and is often modified by the name of the valuable constituent, e.g., "iron ore".

http://purl.org/dc/terms/source.value: Glossary of Geology. 5th Edition, AGI - online

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: Rocks of which the constituents are newly formed particles that have never been constituents of previously formed rocks and that are not the products of alteration or replacement, esp. igneous rocks formed directly by solidification from a magma

http://purl.org/dc/terms/source.value: Glossary of Geology. 5th Edition, AGI - online

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: Rocks composed of particles derived from the erosion or weathering of pre-existing rocks, such as residual, chemical, or organic rocks formed of detrital, precipitated, or organically accumulated materials; specif. clastic sedimentary rocks.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/source.value: Glossary of Geology. 5th Edition, AGI - online

http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#defi.value: The rock adjacent to, enclosing, or including a vein, layer, or dissemination of ore minerals. It is commonly altered by epigenetic processes. The term implies more specific adjacency than host rock or country rock.

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: This file contains the CGI Earth Resource Material Role vocabulary, as defined by the IUGS Commission for Geoscience Information (CGI) Geoscience Terminology Working Group. This scheme describes concepts used to specify the relationship of Earth materials to a resource occurrence. By extension, this vocabulary includes all concepts in this conceptScheme, as well as concepts in any previous versions of the scheme.
